  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>NACCE</measure>
    <time_frame>12 months clinical follow-up</time_frame>
    <description>rates of Net Clinical Benefit (net adverse clinical and cerebral events, NACCE) at 12 months clinical follow-up. The primary endpoint is defined as the composite endpoint of: death by any cause, myocardial infarction (MI), cerebral vascular accident, and major bleeding (according to the modified REPLACE-2 and GUSTO criteria). The primary endpoint will be assessed only in patients receiving exclusively the Endeavor ZES during index (and staged) procedure.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
